Class Coordinates

java.lang.Object
fr.univlille.iutinfo.game.Coordinates
All Implemented Interfaces:
fr.univlille.iutinfo.cam.player.perception.ICoordinate
public class Coordinates extends Object implements fr.univlille.iutinfo.cam.player.perception.ICoordinate
This class represents coordinates in terms of rows and columns. It implements the ICoordinate interface to enable coordinate management.

Coordinates are used to identify positions in a two-dimensional data structure, such as a grid, matrix, or two-dimensional array. Each instance of the Coordinates class has a row and a column that define the position.
